question.title: What will Alphabet's Q4 2025 constant-currency revenues be in these global regions? (EMEA)
question.description:
Alphabet, parent company of Google, dominates search globally with, as of November 2025, [market share](https://gs.statcounter.com/search-engine-market-share/) of 89% in Europe, 97% in Africa, 91% in Asia, 91% in Oceana, and 93% in South America. These all exceed Google's market share of 85% in the United States. By constant currency revenues, 52 cents of every dollar [received](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1652044/000165204425000014/goog-20241231.htm#iceb58926ff9849d5be7614e3b0f8e836_67) by Google comes from outside of the US.

In the quarter just ended ([Q3 2025](https://s206.q4cdn.com/479360582/files/doc_financials/2025/q3/2025q3-alphabet-earnings-release.pdf)), Alphabet reported \$28.65 billion in constant-currency revenues from EMEA, up 11.84% compared to Q3 2024. It reported \$17.691 billion from APAC, up 19.28% compared to the prior year, and in Other Americas it reported \$6.115 billion, up 7.68%. 

Please find a spreadsheet [here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1IWTphOe2H1dpRTvnMvFMPu9IN_1uBdpVRLqn8gTFZgU/edit?gid=0#gid=0) with Alphabet's global quarterly revenues for each region since the beginning of 2020, including year-over-year growth calculations.

question.resolution_criteria:
This question is a subquestion of a group question. This subquestion specifically pertains to (and resolves according to) the option 'EMEA'. The resolution criteria for the parent question is below. 

This question resolves as the revenues in constant currency [reported](https://abc.xyz/investor/) by Alphabet for these geographic regions in the fourth quarter of 2025:

* EMEA (Europe, the Middle East, and Africa)
* APAC (Asia-Pacific)
* Other Americas (Canada and Latin America)
